> Kris or is it Pujo?
> 	As a member of this list you are free to post
> digital photographs in 
> the members photo area. From your description it is
> very hard to say 
> anything at all about your sword, however if you can
> share some 
> pictures with us there are people on the list who
> are happy to share 
> their knowledge. You'll need several photos; one of
> the whole sword in 
> it's scabbard, one of the naked tang/signature, one
> of the backside of 
> the tang, and if possible one of the first five or
> six inches above the 
> hamachi and one of the kissaki (preferably a close
> up showing the 
> hamon). Kantei from photos is always pretty dicey
> but as I said we are 
> happy to share what we can.
> Tom
> 
> PS the powder is likely uchiko which is used to
> clean the blade...
